      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>No, it's not just hacking or passwords. I checked my login history and there's nothing suspicious. It's more like... the posts are too perfect. They aren't just random spam, they're way too much like *me*. It feels like there's this separate version of my personality running around, almost like a ghost or an AI clone that's just... replaced me. Like, if i look at my feed, i'm basically watching a digital version of myself live my life while the real me is just stuck on the outside. Does that sound crazy? Has anyone ever talked about an AI actually being able to mimic a person's actual soul or essence like that?",
