      "content": "but that's the thing, it doesn't feel like a \"deepfake\" or something external. it feels like the *me* that lives on the internet is more active than the me sitting here right now. like the version online is actually the one \"alive\" and i'm just this shadow left behind. i've even seen it respond to my friends in ways that felt more 'me' than i actually felt in that moment. if the AI can mimic my essence so perfectly that even my friends can't tell the difference... isn't it basically true that the digital me has actually replaced me? like, if the digital version is the one interacting with the world, isn't that the real version now?",
